      "title": "Session summary: food-store-sdd",
      "content": "## Goal\nComplete Change 3: auth-roles implementation for Food Store backend with JWT authentication, bcrypt password hashing, RBAC (admin/customer roles), and rate limiting\n\n## Instructions\n- Language: Python backend (FastAPI)\n- Auth tech: Passlib + bcrypt, python-jose (JWT HS256), slowapi (rate limiting)\n- Rate limiting: 5 attempts / 15 min on /auth/login per IP\n- Roles: 2 only (admin, customer); admin inherits customer perms\n- Passwords: Min 8 chars, 1 uppercase, 1 digit, 1 special char (!@#$%^\u0026*)\n- Backend-only for this change (frontend deferred)\n- PostgreSQL for production; in-memory repository for dev\n\n## Discoveries\n- Passlib + bcrypt has version incompatibility issues on Windows Python 3.12 (bcrypt module missing __about__ attribute)\n- JWT approach: separate access_token (15 min) + refresh_token (7 days) for security\n- Refresh tokens stored in-memory dict for logout invalidation (not Redis)\n- Rate limiting via slowapi middleware on /login endpoint\n- InMemory repository for dev; PostgreSQL implementation ready for later switch\n- Password validation: Pydantic validators on schemas\n- Roles: Only 2 (admin, customer) for MVP; admin assigned only via DB\n\n## Accomplished\n- ✅ Setup \u0026 dependencies: backend/ structure, requirements.txt, FastAPI + slowapi\n- ✅ Usuario model \u0026 repository: models/usuario.py, IUsuarioRepository + InMemoryUsuarioRepository + PostgreSQLUsuarioRepository\n- ✅ Password security: password_service.py (hash_password, verify_password, validate_password_strength)\n- ✅ JWT token services: token_service.py (create_access_token/refresh_token, decode_token, validate_token, revoke_refresh_token)\n- ✅ Pydantic schemas: auth_schema.py, user_schema.py with validators\n- ✅ Auth endpoints: POST /auth/register, /auth/login (with rate limiting), GET /auth/me, POST /auth/refresh, POST /auth/logout\n- ✅ JWT middleware: get_current_user dependency, @require_role decorator, CurrentUser class\n- ✅ Integration \u0026 config: FastAPI app, CORS, auth router registered, env.py with JWT vars\n- ✅ Testing: 50+ test cases across multiple test files\n- ✅ Documentation: AUTHENTICATION.md with flow diagrams and examples\n- 🔴 Group 11: Final verification (pytest run encountering bcrypt version issues)\n\n## Discovered Issues\n- pytest tests failing due to passlib/bcrypt incompatibility on Windows Python 3.12\n- ValueError: password cannot be longer than 72 bytes from bcrypt during passlib initialization\n- Need to resolve environment issue before running full test suite\n\n## Next Steps\n1. Fix bcrypt/passlib version compatibility issue\n2. Run `pytest tests/` to verify all 50+ tests pass\n3. Manual test: register → login → get /auth/me with token → logout → verify refresh_token revoked\n4. Verify rate limiting: 5 login attempts succeed, 6th returns 429\n5. Verify password_hash never appears in response bodies\n6. Archive Change 3 in OPSX\n7. Begin Change 4: categoria-crud\n\n## Relevant Files\n- backend/main.py — FastAPI app, router registration\n- backend/routers/auth.py — All 5 auth endpoints\n- backend/services/password_service.py — Passlib + bcrypt hashing\n- backend/services/token_service.py — JWT token generation/validation\n- backend/middleware/jwt_middleware.py — CurrentUser dependency, @require_role decorator\n- backend/schemas/auth_schema.py — Pydantic request/response models\n- models/usuario.py — Usuario model with email, role, timestamps\n- repositories/usuario_repository.py — Repository interfaces and implementations\n- config/env.py — JWT configuration\n- tests/test_*.py — 50+ test cases\n- AUTHENTICATION.md — Auth documentation",
