      "content": "**What**: Resolved bcrypt/passlib version incompatibility and fixed rate limiter causing test failures. All 62 tests now pass.\n\n**Why**: \n- Passlib 1.7.4 + bcrypt 5.0 had initialization errors due to `bcrypt.__about__` missing\n- Rate limiter was holding state across tests causing 429 errors on subsequent login attempts\n- /auth/me and /auth/logout endpoints weren't receiving Authorization headers correctly\n\n**Where**:\n- backend/services/password_service.py — Refactored to use bcrypt directly instead of Passlib\n- backend/routers/auth.py — Added Header import and fixed /auth/me, /auth/logout to use Header() for Authorization parameter\n- tests/conftest.py — Created new file with pytest_configure hook to mock rate limiter before module imports\n- tests/test_auth_endpoints.py — Converted global client to fixture, added client parameter to all test methods\n\n**Learned**:\n- Passlib has version conflicts with newer bcrypt; using bcrypt directly is simpler and more reliable\n- Pytest fixtures run AFTER module imports, so pytest_configure hook needed for early patching\n- FastAPI requires Header() or Header(None) to extract HTTP headers; simple function parameters don't work\n- Rate limiters persist state across test runs unless properly reset or mocked\n- Creating fresh TestClient per test (via fixture) prevents cross-test pollution",
