n## Key Implementation Details\n- Password service: bcrypt.hashpw() with automatic salt generation, bcrypt.checkpw() for verification\n- Token service: separate access_token (15 min) + refresh_token (7 days), in-memory revocation store\n- Rate limiter: slowapi @limiter.limit(\"5/15 minutes\") on /auth/login endpoint\n- JWT payload: sub (user_id), email, role, exp, iat, type (\"access\"|\"refresh\")\n- Endpoints all return proper HTTP status codes (201 for register, 200 for success, 401 for auth errors, 429 for rate limit)\n- Tests isolated with per-test fixtures for client, usuario repo reset, token service reset\n- pytest_configure hook mocks Limiter.limit() method globally before test collection\n\n## Relevant Files\n- backend/services/password_service.py — Bcrypt-based hashing/verification/validation\n- backend/services/token_service.py — JWT token generation/validation/revocation\n- backend/routers/auth.py — All 5 auth endpoints with proper Header() parameters\n- backend/middleware/jwt_middleware.py — get_current_user dependency, @require_role decorator\n- backend/schemas/auth_schema.py — Pydantic models with validators\n- models/usuario.py — Usuario model with email, role, timestamps\n- repositories/usuario_repository.py — InMemory + PostgreSQL implementations\n- tests/conftest.py — pytest_configure hook, fixtures for repo/token/limiter reset\n- tests/test_auth_endpoints.py — 13 tests, now with per-test client fixtures\n- openspec/changes/archive/2026-05-06-auth-roles/ — Complete archived change with all artifacts\n\n## Next Steps\n- Initialize Change 4 (categoria-crud) which depends on auth-roles\n- Implement CRUD operations for food categories using RBAC system\n- Continue test-driven development pattern\n- Archive each change after completion",
