      "content": "**What**: Created PalitosCounter React component with SVG rendering of traditional \"palitos\" (stick) scoring system for Argentine Truco game.\n\n**Why**: Improve UI aesthetics and cultural authenticity by adding visual representation of scoring aligned with the game's traditional stick-counting system. Provides better visual feedback when scores change.\n\n**Where**: \n- `src/components/PalitosCounter.jsx` — main component (PalitoGroup + PalitosCounter)\n- `src/components/PalitosCounter.css` — styling with animations and responsive design\n- `src/components/TeamScore.jsx` — updated to integrate PalitosCounter\n- `src/components/TeamScore.css` — updated layout for palitos display\n\n**Learned**: \n- SVG approach is cleaner than CSS borders for diagonal stick rendering\n- useRef + useEffect pattern tracks score changes and triggers animations only on increment\n- color-mix() CSS function provides elegant opacity control for \"ghost\" sticks\n- Mobile scaling (75%) on viewport \u003c 400px handled via transform: scale()\n- PalitosCounter integrates seamlessly into existing TeamScore component\n- Build passes with zero warnings — component is production-ready",
