      "content": "## Goal\nImplement Change 7 (refactor-categoria-ingrediente): Extract CategoryService and IngredientService from routers to follow the Repository + UoW + Service Layer pattern consistently across all CRUD modules.\n\n## Instructions\n- Repository + UoW + Service Layer is the architectural standard for this project\n- All services must validate inputs and raise ValueError with descriptive messages\n- Routers must only handle HTTP concerns (auth, response formatting, exception mapping)\n- Exception mapping: \"ya existe\" → 409, \"no existe\" → 404, \"en uso\" → 409, other ValueError → 400\n- All docstrings must be comprehensive\n- Tests should use mocks for unit tests, real UoW for integration tests\n- When archiving, sync delta specs to main specs\n\n## Discoveries\n- ✅ ProductRepository needed `count_by_category()` and `count_by_ingredient()` methods to validate constraints\n- ✅ CategoryService and IngredientService follow identical patterns (validation → repository calls → UoW commit)\n- ✅ Exception mapping in routers is straightforward: catch ValueError, inspect message, map to HTTP status\n- ✅ Both routers had business logic directly in endpoints - now cleanly separated\n- ✅ InMemoryUnitOfWork supports the pattern well; no PostgreSQL-specific changes needed\n- ✅ Tests can be written comprehensively with pytest + mocks for services, TestClient for endpoints\n\n## Accomplished\n- ✅ **CategoryService** (backend/services/categoria_service.py): 160 lines\n  - create_categoria(nombre, descripcion) with validations (empty, duplicate, length)\n  - update_categoria(id, nombre, descripcion) with duplicate check (except self)\n  - delete_categoria(id) with product usage check (count_by_category)\n  - get_categoria(id)\n  - list_categorias(skip, limit, search)\n  - All methods raise ValueError with specific messages for error handling\n\n- ✅ **IngredientService** (backend/services/ingrediente_service.py): 280 lines\n  - create_ingrediente(nombre, unidad_medida, cantidad_stock, cantidad_minima, descripcion, categoria_id)\n  - Validates: empty name, duplicate, unidad_medida in {gramos, litros, unidades, kilos, mililitros}, non-negative stock/minima\n  - update_ingrediente(id, ...) with all validations\n  - delete_ingrediente(id) with product usage check (count_by_ingredient)\n  - get_ingrediente(id)\n  - list_ingredientes(skip, limit, search, unidad_medida, categoria_id)\n  - get_stock_history(id) returns history from repository\n\n- ✅ **ProductRepository updates** (repositories/producto_repository.py)\n  - Added count_by_category(category_id) to IProductRepository interface\n  - Added count_by_ingredient(ingredient_id) to IProductRepository interface\n  - Implemented both in InMemoryProductRepository using _category_index and _ingredient_index sets\n\n- ✅ **Refactored categorias.py router** (backend/routers/categorias.py): 224 lines\n  - Import CategoryService and instantiate with UoW\n  - POST /categorias: use service.create_categoria(), map ValueError to 409 if \"ya existe\" else 400\n  - GET /categorias: use service.list_categorias()\n  - GET /categorias/{id}: use service.get_categoria(), map ValueError \"no existe\" to 404\n  - PUT /categorias/{id}: use service.update_categoria(), map ValueError to 404/\"no existe\", 409/\"en uso\"\n  - DELETE /categorias/{id}: use service.delete_categoria(), map ValueError appropriately\n  - All business logic removed from router\n\n- ✅ **Refactored ingredientes.py router** (backend/routers/ingredientes.py): 298 lines\n  - Same pattern as categorias.py with IngredientService\n  - POST /ingredientes, GET /ingredientes, GET /ingredientes/buscar, GET /ingredientes/{id}, PUT, DELETE, GET /historial-stock\n  - All exception mapping in place\n  - All business logic removed\n\n- ✅ **Unit tests for CategoryService** (backend/tests/test_categoria_service.py): 150 lines\n  - 30 test cases covering: create (valid, empty, duplicate, too long), update (valid, not found, duplicate), delete (not in use, in use, not found), get, list\n  - Uses pytest fixtures with mock UoW\n  - No FastAPI mocking needed\n\n- ✅ **Unit tests for IngredientService** (backend/tests/test_ingrediente_service.py): 160 lines\n  - 27 test cases covering: create (valid, validations), update, delete, get, list (with filters), stock history\n  - Same mock-based approach\n\n- ✅ **Integration tests for categorias endpoints** (backend/tests/test_categoria_endpoints.py): 180 lines\n  - Tests all 5 endpoints (POST, GET list, GET /{id}, PUT, DELETE)\n  - Verifies correct HTTP status codes (201, 200, 404, 409)\n  - Uses TestClient and admin_headers fixture\n\n- ✅ **Integration tests for ingredientes endpoints** (backend/tests/test_ingrediente_endpoints.py): 210 lines\n  - Tests all 7 endpoints including /buscar and /historial-stock\n  - Comprehensive status code verification\n  - Same TestClient + fixture pattern\n\n- ✅ **Updated tasks.md**: Marked 91/102 tasks complete (sections 1-9 done, 10-11 pending)\n\n- ✅ **Git commit** created: \"refactor: extract CategoryService and IngredientService from routers\"\n  - 10 files changed, 1817 insertions\n  - Includes all services, tests, router refactors, repository updates\n\n## Next Steps (for next session)\n1. **Task 10.3**: Run all existing tests to ensure no regressions\n   - Command: `pytest backend/tests/` (may need to install pytest if not present)\n   - Verify both new tests and any existing tests pass\n   \n2. **Task 10.4**: Verify API contracts identical\n   - Compare old vs new endpoint responses for identical structure/fields\n   - Verify all error codes match spec (400, 404, 409)\n   \n3. **Task 10.5**: Code review CategoryService + IngredientService\n   - Check for correctness, edge cases, missing validations\n   - Verify exception handling is comprehensive\n   \n4. **Task 10.6**: Verify UoW injection is clean\n   - Confirm no global state in services\n   - Check that UoW is passed as constructor parameter (it is)\n   \n5. **Task 11.1**