      "content": "**What**: All 20 backend tests for sprint-5-checkout-pedidos now pass (20/20).\n\n**Why**: Several test file bugs fixed after conftest was rewritten to use make_transient():\n\n1. `service.py` docstring contained literal \"session.commit()\" string → smoke test caught it → changed wording\n2. `test_idempotency.py`, `test_rollback.py`: used `client_pedidos.id` but fixture now returns plain int → changed to `client_pedidos`\n3. `test_multi_item.py`, `test_rollback.py`: accessed `p2.id`, `p3.id` AFTER `client_headers(client)` which closes shared session, detaching objects → captured `p2_id = p2.id` BEFORE the HTTP call\n4. `test_no_decrementa_stock.py`: `session.refresh(make_transient_obj)` fails (\"not persistent\") → replaced with `session.get(Produto, produto_disponivel.id)` \n5. `test_snapshot_inmutable.py`: `session.add(make_transient_obj)` causes INSERT → UNIQUE constraint → re-fetch by ID: `p = session.get(Produto, id)` then modify\n\n**Pattern**: Any object accessed AFTER an HTTP request must either be: (a) plain int/value captured before, (b) re-fetched by ID after, or (c) make_transient before. Never session.add() a make_transient object — use session.get() to re-attach.\n\n**Where**: backend/tests/pedidos/*.py, backend/app/modules/pedidos/service.py",
