      "title": "ReclamApp Meta API Rate Limits \u0026 Insights Sync Analysis",
      "content": "**What**: Exhaustive analysis of Meta Graph API rate limit handling for insights synchronization in ReclamApp backend\n\n**Key Findings**:\n\n1. **Backoff/Retry Mechanism** (service.py lines 861-898):\n   - Exponential backoff: 1s, 2s, 4s, ... (2^attempt)\n   - Max retries: 3 (total 4 attempts: initial + 3 retries)\n   - Max backoff: 60s (capped)\n   - Applied only to MetaRateLimitError, not HTTP 429 (429 fails immediately at transport)\n   - Transport layer (5xx errors): exponential backoff with different strategy\n   - Dry run test available: test_sync_rate_limit_retries (succeeds after 3rd call)\n\n2. **Rate Limit Error Codes** (_errors.py lines 22):\n   - Code 4: Application-level rate limit\n   - Code 17: User request limit reached\n   - Code 32: Call limit exceeded\n   - Code 613: (Graph API limit)\n   - Code 80004: User request limit\n   - HTTP 429: Standard rate limit (not retried at transport)\n\n3. **HTTP Retry Logic** (_transport.py lines 25, 165-169):\n   - Only 5xx (502, 503, 504) are retried with 2^attempt backoff\n   - HTTP 429 raises immediately without retry\n   - Rate limit errors get usage_pct from headers if present\n\n4. **Usage Header Parsing** (_transport.py lines 28-64):\n   - Parses X-App-Usage and X-Business-Use-Case-Usage headers\n   - Extracts call_count, total_cputime, total_time percentages\n   - Warns at \u003e= 90% usage\n   - No proactive throttling based on usage (only logging)\n\n5. **Insights Sync Flow** (service.py lines 613-833):\n   - Configured lookback: SYNC_INSIGHTS_LOOKBACK_DAYS (default 1 day)\n   - Calculates date_start = today - lookback_days\n   - Calculates date_stop = today - 1 (always excludes today)\n   - Calls get_insights() per campaign, adset, ad (NOT account-level)\n   - Three separate sync methods: campaign_insights, adset_insights, ad_insights\n   - Each insight row is upserted individually (snapshot per date + entity)\n   - NO async jobs, NO batch processing - sequential HTTP calls\n\n6. **Parameters in get_insights()** (client.py lines 146-181):\n   - node_id: campaign, adset, or ad ID\n   - level: \"campaign\", \"adset\", \"ad\"\n   - time_range: dict with \"since\" and \"until\" (YYYY-MM-DD), JSON-encoded\n   - date_preset: alternative to time_range (e.g., \"last_7d\")\n   - breakdowns: optional breakdown dimensions\n   - Default fields: date_start, date_stop, spend, impressions, reach, clicks, cpc, cpm, ctr\n   - Pagination: automatic via paging.next cursors (up to 50 pages max)\n\n7. **Pagination** (client.py lines 187-230):\n   - Follows paging.next URLs automatically\n   - Cap at max_pages (default 50) - raises MetaAPIError if exceeded\n   - Per-endpoint pagination, not global\n\n**HTTP Call Estimate for 90-day sync**:\nLet's assume:\n- Num campaigns: C\n- Num adsets: A  \n- Num ads: D\n- Avg pagination pages per insights call: P (typically 1-2)\n\nTotal HTTP calls:\n= 1 (list campaigns)\n+ C * (1 list adsets + P insights per adset)\n+ C*A * (1 list ads + P insights per ad)\n+ D * (P insights per ad)\n+ 1 (list creatives)\n= 1 + C + C*P + C*A + C*A*P + D*P + 1\n≈ 2 + C*(1 + A*(1 + P)) + D*P + C*P*A\n\nFor typical mid-size account (10 campaigns, 50 adsets, 500 ads):\n≈ 2 + 10 + 10*50 + 10*50 + 10*50*1.5 + 500*1.5\n≈ 2 + 10 + 500 + 500 + 750 + 750\n≈ 2512 calls (WITHOUT rate limiting)\n\nWith 90-day lookback, insights are called 90 times per entity (one per day range). No - actually SINGLE call with time_range spanning 90 days. So:\n= Initial structure calls (campaigns/adsets/ads/creatives): ~2000\n+ Campaign insights (C calls): 10\n+ Adset insights (C*A calls): 500\n+ Ad insights (D calls): 500\n= ~3010 calls total\n\n**Rate Limit Protections Implemented**:\n1. Exponential backoff on MetaRateLimitError (3 retries)\n2. Usage header monitoring (warnings only, no action)\n3. Transport-level 5xx retry\n4. Per-level error logging (doesn't abort on single failure)\n5. Max pages cap per endpoint\n\n**Rate Limit Risks Identified**:\n1. NO proactive rate limit check - fires requests blindly\n2. NO throttling between requests (inter_level_pause is optional, default 0.0)\n3. NO retry on HTTP 429 (immediate failure)\n4. Paging can spike calls if insights have pagination\n5. Usage warnings don't trigger slowdown\n6. If 90-day sync fires, 3000+ calls hit API in minutes, likely exceeding rate limits\n7. No Async Insights Jobs API integration (would be recommended for bulk operations)\n8. Retry exhaustion is logged but sync continues (partial success possible)\n\n**Meta API Official Limits** (standard):\n- Application level: 200 calls per hour (for public apps, varies by tier)\n- Ad Account level: 120 calls per minute (typical)\n- Business Account: 1000 calls per minute (in burst)\n- Insights endpoint: Subject to same limits, not special-cased\n- Estimated time to regain access: extracted from error_data.estimated_time_to_regain_access\n\n**Configuration Used**:\n- meta_api_max_retries: 3 (from config.py)\n- meta_api_timeout_seconds: 30\n- meta_api_max_pages: 50\n- sync_insights_lookback_days: 1 (default, configurable)\n- sync_inter_level_pause_seconds: 0.0 (no throttle between levels)\n\n**Learned**:\n- Backoff is exponential with hard cap, respects Meta's estimated_time_to_regain_access when present\n- 90-day sync would require ~3000 API calls, likely hitting limits immediately without Async Jobs\n- No batch/async job support - synchronous model is inefficient for bulk insights\n- Usage headers are parsed but only logged, no defensive action taken\n- Retry logic is per-level, not global (if campaigns fail, adsets still attempted)\n- MetaRateLimitError codes include some uncommon codes (613, 80004) handled correctly",
