      "title": "Session summary: reclamapp",
      "content": "## Goal\nImplement `analytics-snapshot-denorm` change: add `snapshot_date` and entity_id as denormalized columns to 15 child snapshot tables, update services/repos to populate them, and add breakdown support to the backfill job.\n\n## Discoveries\n- All 15 child snapshot models had identical structure (snapshot_id FK + action_type + nullable value) with no snapshot_date or entity_id — required migration with NULL→backfill→NOT NULL pattern\n- Migration uses UPDATE...FROM JOIN to backfill existing rows from parent insight snapshots\n- `SyncService._replace_children_of_kind` is the central method for inserting child rows — extending its signature to accept `snapshot_date` + `entity_id` + `entity_col_name` was the cleanest approach\n- `BackfillRepository._replace_children` helper needed `snapshot_date` and entity_id threaded through all 16 `replace_*` method signatures\n- `InsightBackfillJob` model needed `include_breakdowns` field added with `server_default=false` (Boolean NOT NULL)\n- `_ingest_ad_breakdowns` in BackfillService mirrors `SyncService._sync_ad_breakdowns` but operates per-entity within the ingestion loop\n\n## Accomplished\n- ✅ 16 model files updated with `snapshot_date` + entity_id columns and Index on `(entity_id, snapshot_date)` — campaigns/models/, adsets/models/, ads/models/\n- ✅ Alembic migration `5f0842697ddf` — adds columns nullable, backfills via JOIN, alters NOT NULL, adds FK constraints, adds indexes, adds `include_breakdowns` to `insight_backfill_jobs`\n- ✅ `SyncService._replace_children_of_kind`, `_replace_campaign_children`, `_replace_adset_children`, `_replace_ad_children` updated to propagate `snapshot_date` + entity_id\n- ✅ All 16 `BackfillRepository.replace_*` methods updated with new params\n- ✅ `BackfillService._ingest_results` passes `snap.snapshot_date` and `entity.id` to all replace calls; calls `_ingest_ad_breakdowns` after ad level when `job.include_breakdowns is True`\n- ✅ `InsightBackfillJob.include_breakdowns` field added; `BackfillTriggerRequest.include_breakdowns` added; `trigger_backfill` persists flag\n- ✅ `BackfillService._ingest_ad_breakdowns` implemented with delete-then-insert per `(ad_id, snapshot_date)` using 7 breakdown dims\n- ✅ Tests updated and passing — 966 total, 0 failures\n- ✅ All 25 tasks marked complete in tasks.md\n\n## Next Steps\n- `/opsx:archive analytics-snapshot-denorm` to archive the change\n\n## Relevant Files\n- `backend/app/features/campaigns/models/campaign_*_snapshot.py` (5 files) — added snapshot_date + campaign_id + Index\n- `backend/app/features/adsets/models/adset_*_snapshot.py` (5 files) — added snapshot_date + adset_id + Index\n- `backend/app/features/ads/models/ad_*_snapshot.py` (6 files incl. video_metric) — added snapshot_date + ad_id + Index\n- `backend/app/features/sync/service.py` — _replace_children_of_kind, _replace_*_children updated\n- `backend/app/features/backfill/repository.py` — all replace_* methods updated\n- `backend/app/features/backfill/service.py` — _ingest_results, _ingest_ad_breakdowns\n- `backend/app/features/backfill/models/insight_backfill_job.py` — include_breakdowns field\n- `backend/app/features/backfill/schemas/backfill.py` — BackfillTriggerRequest.include_breakdowns\n- `backend/alembic/versions/5f0842697ddf_add_snapshot_date_entity_id_to_child_snapshot_tables.py` — migration",
