      "title": "Session summary: active-trace",
      "content": "## Goal\nImplement and archive C-09 padron-ingesta-moodle — versioned student roster ingestion with file import (xlsx/csv), Moodle WS client, and full CRUD backend stack.\n\n## Instructions\n- No commitear sin pedido explícito del usuario\n- No buildear automáticamente\n- Tests sin mocks de DB (real PostgreSQL via TEST_DATABASE_URL)\n- Conventional Commits sin Co-Authored-By\n- Governance MEDIO para C-09\n\n## Discoveries\n- Parser extracted to `padron_parser.py` (separate from `padron_service.py`) to stay within the ≤500 LOC per file rule — padron_service with everything inline would have exceeded the limit.\n- Unique partial index `uq_version_padron_activa` on `(tenant_id, materia_id, cohorte_id) WHERE activa = true AND deleted_at IS NULL` is the DB-level safety net for the \"one active version\" invariant, complementing the transactional deactivation in PadronService.\n- RN-05 (\"upsert destructivo sin historial\") is superseded by the versioned model (E6 / C-09). PA-01 resolved in favor of versioned approach. Not yet reflected in KB files (done at archive, but KB edits were not performed this session).\n- Tasks 1.7 (apply migration to test DB) and 9.4 (verify coverage) require a live PostgreSQL environment — they were left as `[ ]` and archived with the change without blocking.\n- Moodle client (`moodle_ws.py`) uses httpx async with 3-retry exponential backoff (0.5s/1s/2s). `MoodleIntegrationError` maps to HTTP 502 in the router.\n- Email in `EntradaPadron` is AES-256-GCM ciphertext; `usuario_id` resolved by `email_hash` match against `UsuarioRepository.get_by_email_hash` — unmatched entries get `usuario_id = NULL`.\n\n## Accomplished\n- ✅ C-09 padron-ingesta-moodle implemented — 46/48 tasks (2 require live DB)\n  - `backend/app/models/version_padron.py` — VersionPadron model\n  - `backend/app/models/entrada_padron.py` — EntradaPadron model (email ciphertext)\n  - `backend/alembic/versions/008_padron_y_moodle.py` — migration with tables, indexes, unique partial index, RBAC seed\n  - `backend/app/repositories/version_padron_repository.py`\n  - `backend/app/repositories/entrada_padron_repository.py`\n  - `backend/app/services/padron_parser.py` — pure CSV/XLSX parser\n  - `backend/app/services/padron_service.py` — preview, confirmar, sync_moodle, ver_padron_activo, vaciar\n  - `backend/app/integrations/moodle_ws.py` — MoodleWSClient + MoodleIntegrationError\n  - `backend/app/schemas/padron.py` — Pydantic v2 schemas\n  - `backend/app/api/v1/routers/padron.py` — 6 endpoints under /api/padron\n  - `backend/app/services/rbac_seed.py` — padron:cargar/ver/vaciar + matrix\n  - `backend/pyproject.toml` — openpyxl + httpx added\n  - `backend/tests/test_padron_*.py` — 6 test files\n- ✅ C-09 archived to `openspec/changes/archive/2026-06-09-c-09-padron-ingesta-moodle/`\n- ✅ Specs synced: `openspec/specs/padron-versionado/spec.md` and `openspec/specs/moodle-integration/spec.md` created\n- 🔲 Tasks 1.7 and 9.4 pending (run `alembic upgrade head` + `pytest --cov` against live DB)\n- 🔲 KB edits pending at archive: mark RN-05 superseded in `knowledge-base/05_reglas_de_negocio.md`, close PA-01 in `knowledge-base/10_preguntas_abiertas.md`\n- 🔲 C-10 calificaciones-y-umbral — next in critical path, now unblocked by C-09\n\n## Relevant Files\n- `backend/app/services/padron_service.py` — main business logic for padrón\n- `backend/app/services/padron_parser.py` — pure CSV/XLSX parser\n- `backend/app/integrations/moodle_ws.py` — Moodle WS client\n- `backend/alembic/versions/008_padron_y_moodle.py` — migration 008\n- `backend/app/api/v1/routers/padron.py` — REST endpoints\n- `openspec/specs/padron-versionado/spec.md` — new main spec\n- `openspec/specs/moodle-integration/spec.md` — new main spec",
