      "title": "Session summary: active-trace",
      "content": "## Goal\nImplement all 34 tasks of C-20 (perfil-y-mensajeria-interna): self-service profile API + internal messaging.\n\n## Instructions\n- No commits unless explicitly requested\n- No auto builds\n- Conventional Commits format without Co-Authored-By\n\n## Discoveries\n- `create_access_token` is the correct function in `app.core.security` (not `create_token`) — test helpers must use that signature: `(user_id, tenant_id, roles, secret_key, expire_minutes)`\n- Pre-existing FastAPI version mismatch causes `Router.__init__() got unexpected kwarg 'on_startup'` — all router imports fail at module level, but tests still run via fixtures that call `create_app()` lazily\n- CUIL immutability: implemented via `PerfilUpdate` schema simply not declaring the field + `extra='forbid'` — no conditional logic needed\n- `MensajeService` must store `_tenant_id` locally rather than reading `self._repo._tenant_id` (private attribute access antipattern)\n- `from_attributes=True` in Pydantic BaseModel allows `model_validate()` to work with Python `@dataclass` instances via getattr\n\n## Accomplished\n- ✅ Added `sexo` + `modalidad_cobro` columns to Usuario model + Alembic migration 017\n- ✅ Created `Mensaje` model (thread_id, remitente_id, destinatario_id, asunto, cuerpo, leido_at)\n- ✅ Extended `UsuarioService.create/update` and `UsuarioDecifrado` with new fields\n- ✅ Created `PerfilService` (resolves user_id from JWT, delegates to UsuarioService)\n- ✅ Created `MensajeRepository` (list_inbox, get_thread, is_participant, mark_thread_read, get_other_participant, get_thread_subject)\n- ✅ Created `MensajeService` (enviar, listar_inbox, leer_hilo, responder)\n- ✅ Created schemas: PerfilResponse, PerfilUpdate (no cuil), MensajeCreate, MensajeResponse, ThreadResponse, RespuestaCreate\n- ✅ Created routers: GET+PATCH /api/perfil and POST+GET /api/inbox + GET /api/inbox/{id} + POST /api/inbox/{id}/responder\n- ✅ Updated UsuarioCreate, UsuarioUpdate, UsuarioResponse schemas with new