      "content": "**What**: Proposed C-21 frontend-shell-y-auth (spec-driven schema). Created proposal, design, 6 spec capabilities, and tasks.md. Validates strict.\n\n**Where**: openspec/changes/c-21-frontend-shell-y-auth/ — proposal.md, design.md, tasks.md, specs/{frontend-scaffold,http-client,frontend-auth,session-management,route-guards,app-shell-navigation}/spec.md\n\n**Key decisions (design.md)**:\n- Greenfield: no frontend/ dir exists yet. Stack: React 18 + TS + Vite + Tailwind + TanStack Query + RHF/Zod + Axios.\n- Session state via React Context + useReducer (no Redux/Zustand). Tokens in localStorage isolated behind a tokenStorage module (migratable to HttpOnly cookie). Risk R1 logged.\n- Refresh transparente: Axios response interceptor on 401, isRefreshing flag + queue → single /api/auth/refresh for N concurrent 401s, retry once, exclude refresh endpoint from retry loop.\n- Routing: React Router with \u003cRequireAuth\u003e/\u003cRequireRole\u003e guards.\n- Testing: Vitest + RTL + MSW (mock backend, not Axios directly).\n\n**Critical discovery**: JWT carries only sub/tenant_id/roles/exp — NOT permissions. Permissions resolved server-side per request. NO effective-permissions endpoint exists. So frontend guards filter by ROLE only; backend 403 is the authoritative authorization gate (fail-closed). Open Question Q1: maybe add an effective-permissions endpoint for C-22+.\n\n**Backend auth endpoints consumed (from C-03 specs)**: POST /api/auth/{login, 2fa/login-verify, refresh, logout, forgot, reset}, GET /api/perfil. Login returns access_token+refresh_token OR partial_token+requires_2fa.\n\n**Governance**: BAJO. **Depends on**: C-04 (RBAC), C-03 (auth). **Next**: /opsx:apply c-21-frontend-shell-y-auth",
